100 Years Ago Today, This is What Was Happening ...

On December 19, 1925, the British government faced mounting pressure over its handling of the Irish Free State, as tensions between loyalists and republicans continued to simmer. In France, the government announced plans to address the rising cost of living, sparking debates in the parliament. Meanwhile, the U.S. Senate prepared for a crucial vote on the controversial McFadden Act, which aimed to regulate banking practices amid ongoing economic recovery efforts.
